title: Grateful Dead Live at Dane County Coliseum on 1973-02-15
description:
Set 1

Loose Lucy, Beat It On Down The Line, Brown Eyed Women, Mexicali Blues, Tennessee Jed, Looks Like Rain, Box Of Rain, Row Jimmy, Jack Straw, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Me & My Uncle, Bertha, Playin' In The Band, Casey Jones

Set 2

Here Comes Sunshine, El Paso, You Ain't Woman Enough, They Love Each Other, Big River, Dark Star-> Eyes Of The World-> China Doll, Promised Land, Sugaree, Sugar Magnolia, E: Uncle John's Band, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text:
Here Comes Some Free Advice Well first off if you have somehow stumbled onto this show
You are going to get an earful of some of my favorite Dead
From probably my Favorite year and in my top 5 of overall shows.
And if you aren't sure how much time you want to invest
just listen to Dark Star>Eyes >China Doll.
Thanks to our tapers for giving us another 2/15/73 entry 

Now with that said I want to turn attention to a less known show 
on the Spring Tour 3/21/73-Utica NY
https://archive.org/details/gd73-03-21.sbd.miller.29263.sbeok.flac
.
What I find mind blowing is :3/21/73
1) It has under 25,000 views
2) it has been favorited only 27 times
3) I was only the 11th Head to review the show
[Yet when I listen with my headphones 
it is every bit as classic as 2/15/73]

For comparison:
Dane County 2/15/73 *
1) It has 926,093 Views
2) 944 Favorites
3) 191 Reviews

* Not to knock 2/15/73 -Madison
CURRENTLY SECOND ALL TIME -by popularity
But just to let you know, there really are some undervalued
and off the beaten track shows that are ever bit as fierce
as the runaway all time favorite shows.
I think I shall call them:
"The shows less traveled"- c. free
